trans-unit.source:
input Data [100];
    hidden H [200] from Data all;
    output Out [10] sigmoid from H all;  

The example illustrates some basic commands as follows:  

-   The first line defines the input layer (named Data), which has 100 nodes, and each node represents a feature in the input examples.

trans-unit.target:
input Data [100];
    hidden H [200] from Data all;
    output Out [10] sigmoid from H all;  

The example illustrates some basic commands as follows:  

-   The first line defines the input layer (named Data), which has 100 nodes, and each node represents a feature in the input examples.

source.ph:
// Define the input layers 
    input Pixels [10, 20];
    input MetaData [7];

    // Define the first two hidden layers, using data only from the Pixels input
    hidden ByRow [10, 12] from Pixels where (s,d) => s[0] == d[0];
    hidden ByCol [5, 20] from Pixels where (s,d) => abs(s[1] - d[1])

target.ph:
// Define the input layers 
    input Pixels [10, 20];
    input MetaData [7];

    // Define the first two hidden layers, using data only from the Pixels input
    hidden ByRow [10, 12] from Pixels where (s,d) => s[0] == d[0];
    hidden ByCol [5, 20] from Pixels where (s,d) => abs(s[1] - d[1])
